The article discusses the importance of investing in career-connected learning and community colleges. The author, who is not specified, recounts a recent visit to Rolling Meadows High School in Chicago, where students showcased their projects in manufacturing and engineering. The author emphasizes the need for students to have clear pathways to good careers and highlights the ripple effect that education has on individuals, families, and communities. They argue that every student deserves the opportunity to attend community college and build a great career. The author mentions the College Promise program, which aims to provide free community college education, and the growth of such programs across the country. They stress the bipartisan nature of this issue and call for continued support and advocacy for free community colleges. The article concludes by stating that community colleges are crucial for economic prosperity and preparing the workforce for the future.